3.comment: Ryan Tannehill actually had a solid game, unlike the last time he battled the Patriots. Thanks to poor tackling by New England, Tannehill went 25-of-38 for 350 yards and 2 touchdowns. He had only a couple of misfires, including 1 pass where he missed an open Jordan Cameron downfield. He also had a dropped interception that Jamie Collins let slip through his hands. However, Tannehill ended the year on an excellent note. The Dolphins need to improve his blocking this offseason.    Another positive sign for the Dolphins: DeVante Parker went off, catching 5 balls for 106 yards and a touchdown. His best reception was a 46-yard grab he made over Logan Ryan.
